  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">USAID Tropical Storm IDA Reconstruction Project - I.N. Jose Maria Peralta Lagos (JMPL) Schools</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this project is to reconstruct the critically damaged Jose Maria Peralta Lagos School in Quezaltepeque, damaged as a result of Tropical Storm Ida in 2009. The project will include the renovation and construction of school buildings, perimeter walls, sidewalks and access ramps. The project also includes demolitions, refurbishments, environmental mitigation works, drainage structures, connections to public utilities, and landscaping. In addition, the project will implement a concurrent engagement strategy with community members to ensure they are actively engaged in the development and maintenance of the school and aware of concepts relating to disaster risk reduction and migration.</narrative>
  </description>
